description: As Elon Musk and Argentina’s Javier Milei champion ambitious plans to dramatically slash the size of government, a similar effort is getting underway across the globe from political leaders with a completely different ideology: Vietnam’s Communist Party.
title: Vietnam’s Communists Join Musk, Milei in Slashing Government

description: Chancellor of the Exchequer Rachel Reeves will become the most senior British official to visit Beijing in 7 years this weekend as she embarks on a mission to deepen economic ties with China against the backdrop of UK market turmoil that threatens to undermine her plans to spur growth domestically.
title: Reeves Bids to Deepen China Ties After Week of UK Market Turmoil

description: Circle Chief Executive Officer Jeremy Allaire said Thursday on X that the stablecoin company contributed tokens worth $1 million to President-elect Donald Trump’s inaugural committee — joining a parade of other CEOs vying for favor as the incoming administration works to form a key crypto industry group.
title: Crypto CEOs Clamor for Access to Trump as Inauguration Day Nears

description: Boeing Co. is donating $1 million to Donald Trump’s inauguration committee, matching the amount it gave when the president-elect first took office in 2017.
title: Boeing Gives $1 Million to Trump Inauguration, Matching 2017

description: President Joe Biden said he was increasing federal assistance to California as the state deals with raging wildfires that have ravaged communities and that he had urged Governor Gavin Newsom to spare no expense in combating the deadly flames.
title: Biden Surges Federal Aid to Address ‘Catastrophic’ Fires

description: Institutional investors would face new restrictions on buying housing units in New York state under a proposal that Gov. Kathy Hochul aims to pass in the state budget due April 1.
title: New York Governor to Target Private Equity Home Ownership

description: This is Washington Edition, the newsletter about money, power and politics in the nation’s capital. Today, White House correspondent Josh Wingrove looks at push and pull between the outgoing president and the incoming administration. Sign up here and follow us at @bpolitics. Email our editors here.
title: Biden Has Trump Fuming Over Executive Actions in Final Days

description: Venezuela opposition leader María Corina Machado was freed after a brief detention in which she was forced to record videos, her party’s office said, concluding a harrowing two-hour stretch after she risked her safety to make her first public appearance in months.
title: Venezuela Opposition Says Leader Machado Free After Arrest

description: President-elect Donald Trump is planning a flurry of executive orders around immigration, energy, federal workers and regulatory reform in the early hours after his Jan. 20 inauguration, part of a sweeping effort to quickly implement his policy agenda upon taking office.
title: Trump Plans Quick Executive Orders on Border, Federal Workers

description: European Commission President Ursula von der Leyen is trying to schedule a meeting with Donald Trump in Florida ahead of the president-elect’s inauguration, according to two people familiar with the matter.
title: EU’s Von Der Leyen Trying to Clinch Meeting With Trump

description: US tech billionaire Elon Musk spoke with Germany’s far-right candidate Alice Weidel on his X social media site in what amounted to an unpaid advertisement for the Alternative for Germany party ahead of a federal election next month.
title: Musk Wades Into German Election, Giving Platform to Far Right

description: President Joe Biden has spent his final weeks in office looking to Trump-proof some of his biggest policy priorities, from environmental protections to Ukraine support and manufacturing subsidies. The incoming president isn’t amused.
title: Biden’s Final Sprint Leaves Trump Stewing, Vowing Reversals

description: Poland’s prime minister said Benjamin Netanyahu will have safe passage and not face arrest if the Israeli premier travels to the country to attend a commemoration of the 80th anniversary of the liberation of Auschwitz this month.
title: Netanyahu Won’t Face Arrest If He Travels to Poland, Tusk Says

description: Banned opposition leader María Corina Machado emerged from hiding to join hundreds of Venezuelans protesting against Nicolás Maduro’s planned inauguration after what they say is a fraudulent reelection.
title: Maduro’s Nemesis Joins Protests Denouncing His Win in Venezuela

description: The UK removed the highest number of foreign criminals and immigration offenders since 2018, after Prime Minister Keir Starmer’s new Labour administration stepped up deportations since winning power in July.
title: UK Removes Highest Number of Immigration Offenders Since 2018

description: Support for joining the European Union is increasing in Iceland after the nation’s new government said it plans to hold a referendum on re-engaging in membership talks.
title: Iceland Sees EU Support Rise as Government Promises Referendum

description: Greenland’s Prime Minister Mute B. Egede called on his people to stand united amid a renewed push for independence and recent interest from US President-elect Donald Trump in the Arctic island.
title: Greenland Premier Tells His People to Unite After Trump’s Push

description: Billionaire Elon Musk expressed doubt that his government efficiency panel in President-elect Donald Trump’s incoming administration will actually be able to achieve $2 trillion in cuts to the US federal budget, backtracking from a lofty target that the tech entrepreneur himself had floated.
title: Musk Now Skeptical DOGE Effort Can Cut $2 Trillion From Budget

description: Microsoft Corp. and Alphabet Inc.’s Google are each donating $1 million to Donald Trump’s inauguration fund, joining the roster of technology companies shelling out to back the incoming US president’s festivities later this month.
title: Microsoft, Google Donate $1 Million Each to Trump Inauguration

description: Sub-Saharan Africa’s economic growth is expected to improve to an average 4.2% this year from an estimated 3.8% in 2024, boosted by investments in energy and infrastructure and an expanded services sector, according to Moody’s Ratings.
title: Sub-Saharan Africa Economies Well Placed for 2025, Moody’s Says

description: The administrator of Rene Benko’s bankrupt luxury property unit is asking former supervisory board members to acknowledge their role in causing at least €1 billion ($1.03 billion) of alleged damages by failing to practice proper oversight.
title: Signa Prime Administrator Blames Board for €1 Billion of Damages

description: Manhattan prosecutors urged the US Supreme Court to allow President-elect Donald Trump’s sentencing in his hush-money case to proceed as planned on Friday, saying “there is no basis for such intervention.”
title: NY Prosecutors Ask Supreme Court to Let Trump Sentencing Proceed

description: President-elect Donald Trump has justified his threat of 25% tariffs on Canada by pointing to the US trade deficit. Top Canadian economists have a response to that: it’s all because your country wants cheap oil.
title: ‘What Are You Complaining About?’: Economists Assail Trump’s Canada Trade Claims

description: The sudden resignation of the head of Italy’s secret service has caused a stir in Italian politics, just as Giorgia Meloni’s government negotiated the release of an Italian journalist held by Iran.
title: Italy Spy Chief Resigns Amid Tensions With Meloni Inner Circle

description: Donald Trump hasn’t even taken office, and he is already testing how far the US Supreme Court will yield to his demands as he starts his second term as president.
title: Trump Tests Power With Supreme Court Even Before He’s Sworn In

description: Ivorian President Alassane Ouattara said he would consider seeking a fourth term in office later this year if his party backed his candidacy.
title: Ivory Coast Leader Signals That He’s Mulling a Fourth Term

description: Slovakia’s Prime Minister Robert Fico said he wasn’t ruling out the resumption of gas through Ukraine after a deal between Kyiv and Moscow expired at the beginning of this year.
title: Slovakia’s Fico Pushes EU to Help Restart Ukraine Gas Transit

description: Russian President Vladimir Putin said he would be talking with his Chinese counterpart Xi Jinping by phone soon.
title: Putin Says He’ll Hold Phone Call With China’s Xi Soon

description: Lebanon lawmakers elected army commander Joseph Aoun as the country’s first president in more than two years, picking a US-backed candidate in a sign of Iran’s waning influence in the region.
title: Lebanon Picks US-Backed Aoun as President in Shift From Iran

description: Ukraine’s leader made a plea to press on with support for his war effort 11 days before the inauguration of US President-elect Donald Trump, who has pledged a swift end to the fighting.
title: Zelenskiy Warns It’d Be ‘Crazy to Drop the Ball’ on War Effort

description: Only seven working days remain in the Biden administration, but US Federal Trade Commission Chair Lina Khan still hopes to push a few more cases out the door before she leaves.
title: FTC’s Khan Urges Agency to ‘Stay Aggressive’ After She Goes

description: Chancellor of the Exchequer Rachel Reeves’s deputy said the gilt market is functioning as normal and underlying demand for UK debt is strong, as pressure grows on the British government amid a rise in borrowing costs and wider market selloff.
title: UK Minister Says Gilt Markets ‘Orderly’, Demand for Debt Strong

description: Prime Minister Giorgia Meloni said Italy is in preliminary talks with Elon Musk’s SpaceX to provide secure communications for the government.
title: Meloni Says SpaceX Talks on Telecoms Deal in Exploratory Phase

description: Washington will pay tribute to Jimmy Carter on Thursday, bringing together political rivals in the wake of a rancorous and volatile election to honor a former president praised by both parties for his humility and decency.
title: Carter Funeral Draws Political Rivals Together for Solemn Event

description: Welcome to Balance of Power, bringing you the latest in global politics. If you haven’t yet, sign up here.
title: Flames Engulf US in Final Days of Biden’s Presidency

description: Armenia’s government backed kicking off the process for accession into the European Union, a move that could anger its traditional ally, Russia.
title: Armenia Takes Step Toward EU Accession Talks, Interfax Says

description: Talks between a group of left-wing parties and the French government on the budget are advancing, according to Socialist head Olivier Faure, providing a potential avenue for agreement ahead of Prime Minister Francois Bayrou’s presentation of his policy priorities next week.
title: French Socialist Chief Says Talks Advancing on Budget Compromise

description: Far from saving money on US weapons that are being provided to Ukraine, a Russian victory in the war would require a surge in Pentagon spending of more than $800 billion through 2029, a conservative think tank argues in a new report.
title: Ukraine’s Defeat Would Cost US Far More Than Aid, Group Argues

description: China and Japan are two of Asia’s most powerful nations and the region’s biggest trading partners. Yet centuries of intense rivalry mean their economic embrace can never be taken for granted. Disputes can flare up for all kinds of reasons, from competing territorial claims to the treatment of Japanese nationals living in China.
title: Why Close Trade Partners China and Japan Can’t Get Along

description: Administrators of Iran’s most popular website for tracking the rial’s open-market exchange rate said they took it offline due to cyber attacks and security concerns after criticism from the head of the country’s central bank.
title: Iran’s Top FX Site Shuts Over Cyber Attacks Amid Currency Crisis

description: Another senior member of South Africa’s leftist Economic Freedom Fighters party has quit, dealing it a further blow following election losses and high-profile departures last year.
title: Another Stalwart of South Africa’s Leftist EFF Party Quits

description: Computer chips are the engine of the digital economy, and their growing capabilities are enabling technologies such as generative artificial intelligence that promise to transform multiple industries. Their critical role was highlighted when the coronavirus pandemic disrupted chip production in Asia, tipping global technology supply chains into chaos.
title: Why the World’s Powers Are Locked in a Battle Over Computer Chips

description: Departing Defense Secretary Lloyd Austin spurns criticism from President-elect Donald Trump — and from Trump’s choice to replace him — that the American military has become too “woke,” and champions the value of diversity policies that the next administration wants to scrap.
title: Pentagon Chief Austin Rejects Trump Criticism That US Military Is ‘Woke’

description: When Venâncio Mondlane started out as a political commentator, a nearly seven-foot-tall television journalist was tasked with questioning him. More than two decades later the two are locked in a standoff, with Mozambique’s future at stake.
title: Rebel Pastor, Ex-Television Analyst Upends Mozambican Politics

description: China said the European Union’s measures to shield its companies from foreign subsidies are a barrier to trade and investment, marking the latest clash in the ongoing trade dispute between the two sides.
title: China Announces Results of EU Probe, Hinting at Retaliation

description: President Joe Biden scrapped a planned trip to Rome and Vatican City as California races to contain several fires burning in and around Los Angeles.
title: Biden Cancels Rome Trip as Los Angeles Fights to Contain Fires

description: Malaysia’s governance risk has climbed and will likely stay elevated in the coming quarters as Prime Minister Anwar Ibrahim contends with political tensions, according to BMI, a Fitch Solutions company.
title: Malaysia’s Anwar Faces Mounting Challenges in 2025, BMI Says

description: Sandra Thompson, director of the Federal Housing Finance Agency, will step down on Jan. 19, an agency spokesperson said.
title: FHFA Director Thompson to Step Down on Eve of Trump Inauguration
